reviews.text: This institution needs to review it's policies and cut the red tape. There are many areas of improvement, and opportunity for innovation.  I will only mention a few. This institution has a low graduation rate when compared to it's peers, it is probably because they don't help students succeed, and their policies in essence set a student up to fail rather than succeed; often giving students the runaround. Their staff is not knowledgeable and not professional. This could be addressed through professional development programs implemented at all levels of the institution. I wish I would have not wasted my time and money at this  institution longer to graduate because of arbitrary administrative policies. There are better educational options for less money! Great improvements to the aesthetics and captures the San Luis Valley's natural beauty. This and a few professors are the only positive thing I can share about my experience. Cut the politics and focus on your students!

If you are black you want get accepted , so don't west your money for the application specially if you are applying for rursing . My girl friend has GPA 3.8 plus SNA and work  volunteers and they dint accept and they told her  she didn't require the requirement which is lie .  Even their rates is not good at all they have a one room rates want to Star which is very bad be careful black people it's not for you guys

When I withdrew from Counselor Education, graduate level, I had a 3.3 and the last few semesters my adjuncts were Adams own Phd Candidates.  Both married, with children and their own counseling practices.  Where did they make up for the time?  Well, our courses were actually quite small for a grad program.  One chapter of reading per week, about 700 words of posting max in  discussion and either a 700 word paper and a five pager, or two 25 multiple choice tests.  This is not a graduate level workload!!!!  And the professors were hard to reach at times,  because of their busy schedules.  

And then when I left, all of my accounts were immediately closed!  This means the complaint I wanted to file was impossible, I needed both access to my emails and the inner email on Bulletin Board.  And eerily enough, I had already made one post on the Google Reviews that was not complimentary, with my Adams account.  After they took back the account by installing a new password, my review disappeared!

It's seems there is always something to complain about, however, this University is not one. Outstanding instructors and administrators that care about the student, not easy to find these days. Big beautiful campus on the west side of the Rockies with breathtaking views. Outstanding academic values and one of the best online Counseling programs.

I did research on this school and I found out how much it sucks. I am glad I researched because if I went to this college I would fail in life. People if you think about going to this school, skip it, it would be a waste of money, A LOT OF MONEY, and time.

I go into Burger King on Wednesday because I meet up with a friend. We are at least in Burger King 3 times a month we usually have ice tea. But once in awhile will have something to eat. It's always clean and so are the bathrooms. Which I have to say I love the up-to-date look in Burger King. I especially like the way they designed the bathrooms. I like knowing I have privacy when I go into the bathroom.  Its become our favorite spot to catch up.
I really love their whoppers and their fries. I ordered a 10 piece chicken nuggets for a reasonable price. Always love Burger King anywhere I go and definitely recommend this place.
Usually really fast service, except during lunch hour. Great customer service as well
Had a bacon csburger, the hamburger was the size of a 50ct. Coin with 1 slice of bacon, the top of the bun was bigger than the meal.. very small hamburger, never again. Half star for the French fries
Very Clean and great service.  Awesome people. I felt welcomed.

Loved our time here! In particular, I feel like we got the best deal ever on the buffet! For $12 you got the whole buffet and a chef who would make just about anything off the menu. I even started to ask him "can you make..." before he responded "I can make anything!". It was the best! Had a great Mexican feast at an unbeatable price.

It was great seeing my old employer martin. The waiter was very  argumentive and rude. Didn't check on the table or refills. It was  not a comfortable or pleasant atmosphere. The waiter needs to be fired! Not friendly at all. I don't think I will go back for a long time!
I love calvillos! The staff are amazing and always so helpful! They are very kind to everyone. The food is seriously the best in town

Pablo was probably one of the best waiters I’ve ever had.  At the end we ordered 2 flan and he brought our sopapilla (3 orders) for our kids for free just so our kids didn’t have to sit there without something.  Then he gave us 2 free shots of patron tequila for...being awesome I guess?  Great work Pablo!

Also, the owner stopped by our table too just to say hi, great gem!!
Most hospitable service EVER!! Family owned, over the last 4 years this has been my favorite stop out of every town i pass through, and i travel a ton! Amazing food with so many options!
City market is well organized.Nice displays and fresh produce. They have the friendliest and most helpful staff which makes shopping here a pleasure.
I love this small, intimate grocery market! While they don't have as much of a selection as the larger chains, they picked all the Right merchandise and narrowed my choices to the Best.
I went to city market to pick up some florals for a photo shoot. I was happy with the flowers I was able to find but selection was a little limited.
It was nice shopping at city market. Worker treated me nice
Probably the best produce in the area. Nice door. Clean well-kept. Selection is good. People are nice.
I’m always satisfied when I order from them!! And the delivery time is amazing!!!
Extra. Good. Pizza. And good deals. Too
Very good pizza and excellent customer service.

Traveling through Colorado we stayed at state park near by for 2 weeks. Had pizza from these guys 5 times and I have to admit they made great pizzas every single time. Pizza made to perfection. Best Domino's pizza I ever had. Give them a try you see what I mean
So good best pizza in the vally took kinda long but so worth it

Update: This place closed :-(  Something new is there now. We haven't tried it yet.
----------

We always enjoy stopping here (or at nearby True Grits Steakhouse) when we pass through Alamos.  The menu is very varied. There is something for everyone. And the food is very tasty.  It's a very pleasant surprise in Alamosa. We will return!

Stopped in during a long road trip for lunch. Surprised to find such a great, healthy menu. Everything from pastas to american to authentic Asian dishes all at great prices. Such a needed break from all the fast food junk we have been getting on the road. The service was quick. Only about 5 min from the time we ordered till we were eating.
So good my boys actually got full! Great service and atmosphere. Reasonably priced as well. I highly recommend it.

Healthful Food for Road Trips - It's usually very difficult to find a healthful, quick meal on road trips.  I stopped in here about a year ago to use a restroom, I ended up ordering dinner and loved it! Since that first time I stop there every time I drive through Alamosa. Yay for fresh vegetables on the road!
Decent food. Although Some times You have To pitch pack a lunch to eat while waiting to get your food. Not always though.

Depending on the cook this place can good either good or poor.  Never something you want to say about a restaurant.  I have eaten here many times but with better options in Alamosa or surrounding towns we have given up eating here.

This Mexican Food restaurant is a favorite of the local people here. The food is prepared authentically and is absolutely delicious. The restaurant has recently changed locations and is now conveniently located next to our University. The staff is very friendly and the food is well priced. Great value! 
The owners have had years of experirnce, you can tell.
Very good Mexican food! Small, intimate  place with friendly service and great prices.
Really good I been eating at el charro for 50years
Love it there. They have some good Mexican food.

Just ate at the Hungry Farmer Steakhouse (12/29/2011) and was amazed at the atmosphere and the amount of food. I had the Filet Mignon that was HUGE... The dinner started with Sauteed Mushrooms that were very good and continued with a small salad with Fresh Bread. Then came out the Entree!!! The steak was 20oz of pure heaven... Definitely, the BEST steak I have ever had... Oh did I mention that It was Bacon Wrapped... 2 HUGE slices of Bacon... The prices were very very reasonable if not too low for the quality of the dining experience... I will definitely be returning to THIS Steakhouse!!

I ate at this restaurant and it was alright not the best food yet. I noticed that the waiters and waitress were very unfamiliar with the food that this restaurant serves. I mentioned it to the management. Tony I think was his name, in which i advised him that he should have a training so that his staff would become familiar with the foods and beverages that this restaurant offers. He said that he has meetings all the time but no one in his staff ever has brought up this issue. I told him that I noticed that at another table the customer asked their waiter what was Creme Brule and the waiter could not answer him. Later, after our conversation I could hear him yelling at the waiter that wasn't educated on Creme Brule. Really?? Thats your fault not the waiters...... Get a better Manager.
This place was horrible!!! We bought a rib eye so nasty my husband wouldn't even eat it!!! For the price it was it should have tasted fantastic, horrible service. Don't waste your money hear.
This is the worst place in Alamosa the food is disgusting I went. For breakfast they burn the omelette it was disgusting

Went an ate at the hungry farmer the service sucked we waited for half hr. For our food n when we got it . It was cold . Plus they had two other complains that morning. And the staff told us the manager would call to make it right. Its been 2 weeks i call n they never called me
Friendly service. Food was pretty good considering the location (rural Colorado chinese VS. Chinese food in NYC for example). Lunch prices are quite good for what you get.

My favorite Chinese restaurant of all time. the food is very good quality for an great price. I've never ordered something here and been let down. If you are vegetarian, I recommend the Buddhas Delight. It is fantastic!!
The best Chinese/Vietnamese style food in the area. Everything is very good, in particular their Jampong is highly recommended.

Have been going here for the past 3 years. Wanted to see how the place grew over the years before I rated it. And this is still an amazing place, and has been holding strong. Today, I had dinner here with my family and it was wonderful. 10/10 would recommend.
They have amazing food nice people I love it there best Chinese food I have ever had
It was really good. better than Colorado springs McDonald's.. Everything was fresh thank you

The coke machine is always broken, service is crapy, and the wait is not worth the food. You could go somewhere for better food and get it faster. If you are in a rush go somewhere else, this place is not worth it. To top it all off it is not kid friendly anymore. They have electronic devices that don’t even work half the time. I went once and a baby got run over by a high chair. NOT kid friendly at all.
My weakness! Always a crowd but worth the wait. This location one of the cleanest for being so busy.
Wow looks really nice, so modern, good customer service and they have some good deals.

Nasty food..filthy restaurant .. I am so fed up with the sorry excuse for customer service. I came in today and ordered chicken nuggets, no dipping sauce but 2 packs of mayo, they charged me for the mayo, then tried to give me someone elses food. after they handed my food to the car in front of me, they gave me the same food without replacing it. This place is a horrible location. I will never go back to this location. The sad thing is the owners could care less.
Good food, good service, good prices. So much better than I-hop
Food was good, staff was nice.  Restaurant was cold!  Turn up the heat please
Jacinda does awesome job. And good food
Small but cute cafe and great breakfast want to try lunch
Great people, they thanked us for chosing their restaurant

Never been to this restaurant before. Glad I stopped. I’m from New Mexico. I always go to the other Mexican restaurant across the street. This place serves free warm chips and salsa. The green chile is far the best I’ve ever had. The bathrooms are spotless. The dining areas are also very very clean. Waitstaff is outstanding. Will definitely be back!!
Very clean restaurant. Bathrooms are extremely clean. Great spicy food. Chips come out warm. Waitress was very nice and attentive.

Probably my favorite Mexican restaurant in town. The service is fast and attentive, the food is quality and fresh and there is a ton of seating with good lighting. They have the best margaritas because they aren't heavy on sugary syrup and taste better than any other restaurant in town and probably Colorado.
Every thing was delicious! Fast and friendly staff! We had a party of 8 people and they  service was amazing!! The best authentic Mexican food drove 3 hours for it and will definitely be back!!!
The best green Chile! Nice place. Nice staff. Excellent margaritas!

One of the best Pizza Huts in the area. First folks in so the buffet wasn’t completely out yet. Though the food that was, was absolutely delicious & hot. Staff was friendly & on top of things. Restaurant was pretty clean & well organized.
SO so ummy...and I love supporting young readers -- thanks, Hut! ...did I mention how very yummy the pizza was? Seriously. Good pizza 🥰
Love their pizza! It's the best anywhere. The service at this one is amazing, too!
Food was good and so was the service. Waitress was great also!
Pizza hut has been always the best pizza and love the salads and sauces. Great services as well.

Good place to pick out dinner for the night while you are on the road

Produce and beef was fresh and there was a very wide selection. I briefly eyed a whole trout for under $10 and that looked quite nice. However we already had the steak in hand...

Starbucks inside for a few iced coffees, in and out.
Good place. Prices were fair and the cashier was very helpful. I was from out if town and she helpful and kind! Good store
Lots of great deals here. I lo e that they have sale items from the deli and it is a nice variety. Clean store and spacious.
I love my little, hometown Safeway! All the meat and produce is always wonderfully fresh and there's a nice selection of everything else.

Eh...about 3 out of 4 avocados I buy here are bad. Prices are higher than City Market and there is less variety. The pharmacy staff is great and very helpful, but when it's busy there is only one person helping and the wait can be long. They do have some different items than the other stores have...more varieties of ice cream, for example, and morning star products.

It's good pizza. Personally I have always thought that the pizza out of the pizza trailer always tasted better, but they don't have the trailer anymore - so said. Hopefully, they get it up and running again so. It as very convenient to grab on my way home.

Excellent pizza. So many different varieties and specialty pizzas to choose from. Not just any old pizza place. Gluten free options available. Good place to host a bunch of people or have an office party.

They now offer steaks from 4pm-7pm daily and they are pretty good. I like everything I have tried here. It’s not a chain restaurant so the food can take some time to prepare. Servers are always friendly and helpful.

We've ordered delivery from here a few times. The food is pretty good but the service is not great. 4 out of 5 times, they've forgotten the dipping sauces for the wings, and once they just never showed up;  We called after an hour and a half and they told us the order was never put in. Tonight we tried again and were told it would be about thirty minutes,  we're still waiting after an hour and fifteen minutes.

I give them 5 stars even though they forgot to make our Pizza. When we called them back they were honest about forgetting, hey it happens!  Who ever the manager was, he was very nice, courteous, and professional. The Pizza was delicious! we even had the left overs for breakfast.  We will definitely go back when we are visiting the San Luis Valley!!

One of my favorite restaurants to eat. Everything on the menu is named after a John Wayne movie. I've never had a bad experience their. Some of the best Dam Steaks you will eat. I love their draft Stella in it's own bladder bag system. Always 36 degrees. When i go on vacation. I would driive a thousand miles to eat their. Some places you just wait to get to.😭😢I went there 2 weeks ago and they're closed. What a sad day. BUT... in the Roadway Inn Hotel, there's a Kitchen restaurant,  that has a bar and grill, and the food was Excellent,  you won't be dissatisfied,  That will be my new stop. Very friendly staff.
Absolutly love this place. The steaks are great!! I come here quite often and would recommend eating here to anyone.

Horrible experience. Ordered a moderate steak, server put in the biggest, most expensive steak. When he came to my table to inform me that my "big Jake" (the most expensive one on the menu) would be ready soon I informed him that I did not order that. He checked his pad and realized his error. Sitting right next to the kitchen I heard the cooks response when informed of this. Very loudly she stated that "he ordered it, he will damn well pay for the f***ing thing!". Server explained that it was his error yet she continued her foul ranting so the entire restaurant could here. Wow!! Needless to say I did not eat the steak that was eventually brought to my table. I feared what had been done to it in after what I heard.  This was some time ago, and decided to give them another chance. Equally unsatisfied. Steak was overdone and service was rude

Absolutely the worse steak we've ever ate! The cook isn't to blame though,  it was bad beef! Prices were obscene for what we got! Waitstaff was great. With a restaurant  based on John Wayne...they let the Duke and us both down!
Very good food and great staff well go back again for sure.

Love Wendy's burgers. I think they are so much better than so many of the other burger chains. Got the biggie bag for 5 dollars. It was much less than the way it looks on the ad (mini burger, 4 small nuggets, very little bacon in a sandwich that is advertised to be double stacked. Therefore 4 stars) but nevertheless I left satisfied.

I really like this Wendy's. It's one of my favorite places to grab a quick lunch. Very clean, fast and great customer service. The isn't dripping grease like a couple of other Wendy's restaurants I have been to. Definitely recommend. Also the strawberry lemonade is a must have.
Nice ,fast ,friendly got my food in and out quick good price good food  fish sandwich  2. To be exact disappeared nothing flat
Andrew runs a great day crew they take pride in food quality & customer service which i see almost 3-5 times per week. The best grilled Asiago chicken

Best coffee out of all the other local fast food places, even if they don't serve breakfast they open at 10am if you want an early burger, I recommend a Dave's Double or one of his signature burgers because they're the best!

We stopped here because it was the better rated of two burger joints, and I am so glad we did. The food was really good and the service was super nice. Christine waited on us and she got it perfect. The fries are fantastic, we had a chicken fajita Philly sandwich and a mushroom and Swiss burger. Both were good and came out quickly and the portions are huge. It was the best place to stop after a day on the dunes.

This is a sweet little spot, and right on the main drag. The service was great, and I didn't wait more than a minute for a refill on my drink. The menu has a little (or a lot) of something for everyone, and it was hard to make a decision. I will absolutely be back to try out more options, and see what the bar offerings are.
I have eaten here 3-4 times.  Tried a different burger each time.  They have great food and clean establishment. highly recommend and burger from their menu.

Pleasant surprise on our way home from Santa Fe. The burgers were huge and tasty and the restaraunt is cool. Good service that was fast. We will most definitely stop there again the next time we're in Alamosa!

The food was great and way too much to eat.  The staff was amazing too.  I am in town on business and  I would have never had tried this place had it not been recommended.   I am glad I decided to stop in.  I had the fajita steak and cheese and it was awesome.
